## üîπ *Assignment 5(a): Create a Simple Mobile Website using jQuery Mobile*

---

### üìò *7-Point Theory*

1. *Introduction to jQuery Mobile:*
   jQuery Mobile is a lightweight web framework built on top of jQuery, designed to create responsive and touch-friendly websites optimized for smartphones and tablets.

2. *Mobile-First Design Concept:*
   It follows a ‚Äúprogressive enhancement‚Äù approach, ensuring that the website functions on all devices‚Äîfrom basic phones to advanced smartphones.

3. *Pages and Navigation:*
   In jQuery Mobile, each ‚Äúpage‚Äù is defined inside a <div> with a data-role="page" attribute. Navigation between pages occurs through internal hyperlinks (href="#pageid").

4. *Theming and UI Widgets:*
   jQuery Mobile includes built-in themes, icons, and styles for headers, footers, buttons, lists, and forms, all controlled through data-role and data-theme attributes.

5. *Responsive Layout:*
   The framework automatically adapts elements (buttons, forms, images) to different screen sizes, giving a consistent user experience across devices.

6. *Advantages of jQuery Mobile:*

   * Easy navigation structure
   * Lightweight and fast loading
   * Touch-optimized for mobile devices
   * Supports multiple platforms (Android, iOS, etc.)

7. *Applications:*
   jQuery Mobile is widely used for mobile-friendly dashboards, personal portfolios, small business websites, and simple web apps requiring quick development.

---

### üß∞ *Software Requirements*

* Operating System: Windows 10 / 11
* IDE / Editor: Visual Studio Code, Sublime Text, or Notepad++
* Browser: Google Chrome / Microsoft Edge
* Libraries:

  * jQuery v1.11.1
  * jQuery Mobile v1.4.5
* Internet Connection (for CDN links)

---

### ‚öôÔ∏è *Hardware Requirements*

* Processor: Intel i3 or higher
* RAM: Minimum 4 GB
* Storage: 500 MB free space
* Display: 13‚Äù or larger (recommended for testing layout)
* Mobile Device (optional): For testing responsiveness

---

### üîÑ *Algorithm*

1. *Start*
2. Create an HTML document with the jQuery Mobile framework linked via CDN.
3. Define multiple pages (home, about, projects, and contact) using <div data-role="page">.
4. Add navigation buttons using <a href="#pageid" data-role="button">.
5. Include a header and footer on each page using data-role="header" and data-role="footer".
6. Add images, text, and form elements in respective sections.
7. Apply external CSS to style the elements for visual appeal.
8. Save the file as index.html and open it in a browser.
9. *End*

---

### ‚ö° *Working*

1. When the user opens the *index.html* file in a browser, the home page loads displaying the name ‚ÄúMansi Patil‚Äù and navigation buttons.
2. On clicking ‚ÄúAbout Me‚Äù, ‚ÄúProjects‚Äù, or ‚ÄúContact‚Äù, the app transitions smoothly to the corresponding internal page.
3. The *About* page describes the user‚Äôs skills and learning interests.
4. The *Projects* page lists sample projects using jQuery Mobile‚Äôs listview.
5. The *Contact* page allows visitors to fill out and submit their details.
6. The layout automatically adjusts to screen size‚Äîensuring it looks good on both desktop and mobile.

---

### üíª *Code*

*index.html*

html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <title>Mansi Patil - Portfolio</title>
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">

  <!-- jQuery Mobile -->
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://code.jquery.com/mobile/1.4.5/jquery.mobile-1.4.5.min.css">
  <script src="https://code.jquery.com/jquery-1.11.1.min.js"></script>
  <script src="https://code.jquery.com/mobile/1.4.5/jquery.mobile-1.4.5.min.js"></script>

  <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
</head>

<body>

  <!-- Home Page -->
  <div data-role="page" id="home">
    <div data-role="header" data-theme="b">
      <h1>Mansi Patil</h1>
    </div>

    <div role="main" class="ui-content">
      <img src="https://via.placeholder.com/120" alt="Profile" class="profile-pic">
      <h2>Hello, I'm <span class="highlight">Mansi Patil</span></h2>
      <p>A passionate web developer learning modern web technologies!</p>

      <a href="#about" data-role="button" data-icon="user">About Me</a>
      <a href="#projects" data-role="button" data-icon="grid">Projects</a>
      <a href="#contact" data-role="button" data-icon="mail">Contact</a>
    </div>

    <div data-role="footer" data-position="fixed">
      <h4>&copy; 2025 Mansi Patil</h4>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- About Page -->
  <div data-role="page" id="about">
    <div data-role="header" data-theme="b">
      <a href="#home" data-icon="home">Home</a>
      <h1>About Me</h1>
    </div>

    <div role="main" class="ui-content">
      <p>I'm Mansi Patil, a student who loves creating simple and creative web applications.</p>
      <p>I enjoy learning HTML, CSS, JavaScript, and exploring AWS cloud deployment.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Projects Page -->
  <div data-role="page" id="projects">
    <div data-role="header" data-theme="b">
      <a href="#home" data-icon="home">Home</a>
      <h1>My Projects</h1>
    </div>

    <div role="main" class="ui-content">
      <ul data-role="listview" data-inset="true">
        <li><h2>To-Do List App</h2><p>A simple web app to manage daily tasks.</p></li>
        <li><h2>Restaurant Menu Site</h2><p>Responsive food menu design.</p></li>
        <li><h2>Portfolio Website</h2><p>You're viewing it now! Built with jQuery Mobile.</p></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Contact Page -->
  <div data-role="page" id="contact">
    <div data-role="header" data-theme="b">
      <a href="#home" data-icon="home">Home</a>
      <h1>Contact Me</h1>
    </div>

    <div role="main" class="ui-content">
      <form>
        <label for="name">Name:</label>
        <input type="text" id="name" placeholder="Enter your name">

        <label for="email">Email:</label>
        <input type="email" id="email" placeholder="Enter your email">

        <label for="message">Message:</label>
        <textarea id="message" placeholder="Your message here..."></textarea>

        <input type="submit" value="Send Message">
      </form>
    </div>
  </div>

</body>
</html>


*style.css*

css
body {
  text-align: center;
  font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
}

h1, h2 {
  color: #0078d7;
}

.profile-pic {
  width: 100px;
  border-radius: 50%;
  margin: 10px;
}

.ui-content a {
  margin: 5px 0;
}

form input, textarea {
  width: 90%;
  margin: 5px 0;
  border-radius: 8px;
  padding: 5px;
}

input[type="submit"] {
  background-color: #0078d7;
  color: white;
  border: none;
  padding: 8px;
  border-radius: 8px;
}


---

### ‚úÖ *Conclusion*

This experiment demonstrates how *jQuery Mobile* simplifies the creation of mobile-friendly, multi-page websites using minimal HTML and CSS. By applying built-in data roles and themes, developers can design responsive, touch-optimized interfaces suitable for any device.

---

### üéØ *10 Viva Questions and Answers*

1. *Q:* What is jQuery Mobile?
   *A:* It is a touch-optimized web framework used to create responsive mobile websites.

2. *Q:* What is the purpose of data-role="page"?
   *A:* It defines a new ‚Äúpage‚Äù in a single HTML file.

3. *Q:* Why do we use data-role="header" and data-role="footer"?
   *A:* To create consistent headers and footers across pages.

4. *Q:* What does data-theme="b" do?
   *A:* It applies theme ‚Äúb‚Äù color scheme from jQuery Mobile‚Äôs built-in themes.

5. *Q:* How is navigation handled between pages?
   *A:* Using internal links like <a href="#pageid"> for smooth transitions.

6. *Q:* What is the difference between jQuery and jQuery Mobile?
   *A:* jQuery handles DOM and animations, while jQuery Mobile focuses on mobile UI and navigation.

7. *Q:* Why is meta viewport used in the head section?
   *A:* To ensure proper scaling and responsiveness on mobile screens.

8. *Q:* Can jQuery Mobile websites run offline?
   *A:* Yes, if all required files are stored locally and not via CDN.

9. *Q:* What is the main advantage of jQuery Mobile?
   *A:* It allows rapid development of mobile-friendly sites without needing native app coding.

10. *Q:* What types of apps can be built using jQuery Mobile?
    *A:* Personal portfolios, event dashboards, contact directories, and small-scale web apps.
